passages.text: August 31, 2025 10:20 PM GMT
Gongniu Group Co Ltd | Asia Pacific
Unchanged Impact to our thesis
Source: Company data, Morgan Stanley Research
Unchanged Impact to our thesis
Source: Company data, Morgan Stanley Research
(- ) 2Q25 sales of Rmb4.25bn dipped 7% YoY (+8% QoQ), 15% below MSe, given domestic consumption pressure along with a high base.
(- ) 2Q25 GPM of 43.5% fell 0.1ppts YoY (+2.5ppts QoQ), 0.8ppts below MSe, due mainly to a lower mix of high margin products.
\((- / - )\) 2Q25 OPM of 28.5% (+0.8ppt YoY, +2.8ppt QoQ) is roughly in line with MSe of 28.4%. OP missed MSe by 14% on deleverage.
2Q25 net income of Rmb1.09bn (- 17% YoY, +11% QoQ) missed MSe by 19%.

Gongniu will continue to strengthen its efforts on international market expansion, renewable energy business, smart home ecosystem and new business initiatives on Al infrastructure. We remain Ow, supported by the company's leadership in the sector and balance sheet strength, which provide resilience against macro headwinds.
MORGAN STANLEY TAIWAN LIMITED+ Terence Cheng

We apply a target P/E multiple of 25x to our 2025 EPS estimate, vs its historical range of 18.2- 54.2x since the IPO. Our target P/E multiple is below the mean of 28.7x, which we think is reasonable amid the housing market downturn and tough macro conditions.
- Healthy property cycle in China- Better-than-expected consumption environment in China- Stable raw material costs and favorable FX movement- Increasing pricing power thanks to product innovation
- China housing cycle weakness- Slower-than-expected recovery of consumption in China.- Fluctuations in raw material costs- Market share losses in core businesses
